               <head>Bayāz̤ by Bandah ʻAlī Bāsiṭī Niʻmat’Allāhī</head>
               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/sh89005046 http://id.loc.gov/authorities/sh2008109077">
                  <summary>An anthology of ancient and contemporary verses by Bandah ʻAlī
							Bāsiṭī Niʻmat Allāhī, copied at Lucknow (f. 1r) between 1162/1749 (f.
							203r) and 1178/1764, the date of the author’s inscription on f. 1r. </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_588-item1">
                     <author key="person_f3321">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Bandah ‘Alī Khān Bāsiṭī </persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">بنده علی خان باسطی </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_6996">Bayāz̤ </title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">بیاض</title>
                     <colophon>Undated colophon (<locus>f. 203v</locus>): Copied by <persName role="scr" key="person_f7947">Muḥammad Bāqir ibn Ḥasan
									ʻAskarī</persName>. 
                     </colophon>
                     <note>
                        <p>The work is preceded (<locus>ff. i verso – v recto</locus>) by a
									thematic index. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The khāṭimah (<locus>ff 202v-204r</locus>) contains biographical
									details of the author. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Some marginal additions are in the hand of the compiler (eg. f.
									49r). </p>
                        <p>Note (<locus>f. 1r</locus>) signed by the author, Bandah ʻAlī
									Bāsiṭī Niʻmat’Allāhī, dated 14 Jumada I, 1178 (9 Nov. 1764),
									mentions that this copy of his Bayāz̤ was copied in Lucknow and
									was presented by him to <persName role="fmo" key="person_f7946">Sayyid Nūr ʻAlī</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>This work appears to be substantially the same as Rylands <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7148">
                              <idno>Persian MS 646</idno>
                           </ref>, but different from
									British Library <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_16712">
                              <idno>Delhi Persian 1303</idno>
                           </ref>. 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
